wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# Resume Website - Professional Portfolio & Multi-Format Resume Platform

## Project Introduction

**Purpose Statement**
A modern, accessible, and highly functional portfolio website that showcases professional experience while providing multiple resume formats optimized for different use cases. The platform serves as both a personal brand showcase and a practical tool for job seekers requiring various resume formats.

**Core Goals and Objectives**
- Deliver a visually stunning portfolio with smooth animations and responsive design
- Provide four distinct resume formats: Print, ATS-optimized, Digital, and Portfolio
- Enable real-time ATS compatibility scoring and optimization
- Support role-specific resume customization for different career paths
- Offer Progressive Web App capabilities for offline access and installation
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards across all components

**Target Audience**
- Job seekers targeting software development, data analysis, and automation engineering roles
- Hiring managers and recruiters seeking structured candidate information
- Developers looking for inspiration in modern web design and implementation
- Professionals requiring ATS-friendly documentation for job applications

## Technical Architecture

The project follows a modular, vanilla JavaScript architecture with modern build tooling and automated deployment pipeline.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Main Landing Page] --> B[Router Module]
    A --> C[Theme Manager]
    A --> D[Variant Manager]
    
    B --> E[Navigation System]
    B --> F[Route Detection]
    
    C --> G[Color Themes]
    C --> H[Dark/Light Mode]
    C --> I[Palette Selection]
    
    D --> J[Resume Variants]
    D --> K[Format Switching]
    D --> L[Primary Action Update]
    
    M[PWA Manager] --> N[Service Worker]
    M --> O[Install Prompt]
    M --> P[Offline Support]
    
    Q[ATS Calculator] --> R[Keyword Analysis]
    Q --> S[Compatibility Scoring]
    Q --> T[Improvement Suggestions]
    
    U[Portfolio Enhancer] --> V[Github Stats]
    U --> W[Project Metadata]
    U --> X[External Link Enhancement]
    
    Y[Build System] --> Z[Vite Bundler]
    Y --> AA[ES Modules]
    Y --> BB[Modern Browser Target]
```

**Component Breakdown**
- **Entry Points**: `index.html` main landing page with modular JavaScript imports
- **Core Modules**: ES6 modules for theme management, routing, PWA functionality, and resume variants
- **Static Assets**: CSS frameworks, icons, and responsive design elements
- **Dynamic Content**: JSON-based resume data with automated generation scripts
- **Deployment Pipeline**: GitHub Actions for automated testing, building, and deployment

**Design Patterns**
- **Module Pattern**: ES6 modules for encapsulated functionality
- **Observer Pattern**: Event-driven interactions for theme switching and navigation
- **Factory Pattern**: Dynamic UI component creation for ATS scoring and PWA features
- **Strategy Pattern**: Multiple resume format strategies with unified interface

## Key Implementation

**Main Entry Points**
- `index.html` - Primary landing page with hero section, navigation, and resume variant cards
- `assets/js/main.js` - Core application initialization and theme management
- `assets/js/router.js` - GitHub Pages-compatible routing system

**Core Modules**
- `assets/js/src/theme-manager.js` - Advanced theme switching with color palettes
- `assets/js/src/variant-manager.js` - Resume format selection and primary action management
- `assets/js/src/pwa-manager.js` - Progressive Web App functionality and service worker integration
- `assets/js/src/ats-calculator.js` - Real-time ATS compatibility scoring system
- `assets/js/src/portfolio-enhancer.js` - GitHub integration and project enhancement

**Configuration Approach**
- `vite.config.mjs` - Modern build configuration with GitHub Pages base path
- `package.json` - Comprehensive script definitions for development, testing, and deployment
- `public/manifest.json` - PWA configuration with shortcuts and share targets

**External Dependencies**
- **Build Tools**: Vite 7.2.7 for development server and bundling
- **Testing**: Playwright 1.58.0 for end-to-end testing, Vitest 4.0.16 for unit tests
- **PDF Generation**: Playwright Chromium for automated resume generation
- **Code Quality**: ESLint 9.39.1, Prettier 3.7.4, Husky 9.1.7 for pre-commit hooks

**Integration Points**
- **GitHub Pages**: Automatic deployment through GitHub Actions workflows
- **Google Analytics**: Optional analytics integration for user behavior tracking
- **GitHub API**: Live project statistics and metadata enhancement
- **Service Workers**: Offline caching and installation capabilities

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Interaction] --> B[Event Handler]
    B --> C[Module Processing]
    C --> D[State Update]
    D --> E[DOM Manipulation]
    E --> F[Visual Feedback]
    
    G[File System] --> H[JSON Data]
    H --> I[Resume Templates]
    I --> J[PDF Generation]
    
    K[Build Process] --> L[Vite Compiler]
    L --> M[Bundle Output]
    M --> N[Distribution]
    
    O[GitHub Actions] --> P[Automated Testing]
    P --> Q[Quality Gates]
    Q --> R[Deployment]
```

## Key Features

**Functionality Overview**
- **Multi-Format Resume System**: Four distinct resume formats (Print, ATS, Digital, Portfolio) with role-specific optimizations
- **Advanced Theme Management**: Color palette cycling, dark/light mode with system preference detection
- **Real-Time ATS Scoring**: Interactive compatibility analysis with improvement suggestions
- **Progressive Web App**: Installable application with offline capabilities and service worker caching
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with adaptive layouts for all device sizes
- **Accessibility Compliance**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliant with ARIA labels and keyboard navigation

**Implementation Highlights**
- `public/manifest.json` - PWA configuration enabling app installation and offline functionality
- `assets/js/src/ats-calculator.js` - Intelligent keyword matching and ATS compatibility scoring
- `assets/js/src/portfolio-enhancer.js` - Live GitHub integration with project statistics
- `assets/js/src/pwa-manager.js` - Comprehensive service worker management and update notifications
- `assets/js/src/variant-manager.js` - Dynamic resume format switching with primary action updates

**Feature Architecture**

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Loading
    Loading --> ThemeSelection: User Access
    ThemeSelection --> Navigation: Theme Applied
    Navigation --> ResumeSelection: Route Change
    ResumeSelection --> FormatDisplay: Variant Active
    FormatDisplay --> ATSAnalysis: User Action
    ATSAnalysis --> FormatDisplay: Results Updated
    
    FormatDisplay --> PWAInstall: Install Prompt
    PWAInstall --> FormatDisplay: Installation Complete
    
    Navigation --> OfflineMode: Network Loss
    OfflineMode --> Navigation: Network Restored
```

**Resume Variant System**
- **Print Format**: Standard A4 PDF optimized for traditional applications
- **ATS Format**: Machine-readable structure with keyword optimization
- **Digital Format**: Interactive web-based resume with animations and transitions
- **Portfolio Format**: Showcase of projects with GitHub integration and live statistics

**Advanced Features**
- **Role-Specific Optimization**: Three specialized resume variants for Bioinformatics, Data Business Analyst, and Developer/Testing roles
- **Automated PDF Generation**: Script-based generation ensuring consistency across all formats
- **Performance Monitoring**: Lighthouse CI integration for continuous performance tracking
- **Analytics Integration**: Optional Google Analytics 4 implementation for user behavior insights

**Development Workflow**
- **Automated Testing**: Comprehensive test suite with unit and end-to-end testing
- **Code Quality**: ESLint and Prettier integration with pre-commit validation
- **Continuous Integration**: GitHub Actions workflows for automated building, testing, and deployment
- **Documentation**: Extensive guides for router integration, feature implementation, and contribution workflow

---

**Sources:**
- [package.json](package.json)
- [vite.config.mjs](vite.config.mjs)
- [index.html](index.html)
- [main.js](assets/js/main.js)
- [router.js](assets/js/router.js)
- [theme-manager.js](assets/js/src/theme-manager.js)
- [manifest.json](public/manifest.json)
- [generate-pdf.js](scripts/generate-pdf.js)
- [README.md](README.md)
- [ROUTER_GUIDE.md](docs/ROUTER_GUIDE.md)
- [ats-calculator.js](assets/js/src/ats-calculator.js)
- [portfolio-enhancer.js](assets/js/src/portfolio-enhancer.js)
- [variant-manager.js](assets/js/src/variant-manager.js)
- [pwa-manager.js](assets/js/src/pwa-manager.js)

</blog>
